# README Update Requirement

When you add or change user-visible functionality, update `README.md` in the same task.

## Required README updates

- Add or revise a short description of the new functionality.
- Document any new setup, configuration, environment variables, or permissions.
- Update usage instructions (commands, routes, flows, or screenshots) if behavior changed.
- If no README change is needed, explicitly state why in the final response.

## Examples

```text
Feature: Add QR worker pairing flow
README: Add "Worker Pairing" section with steps and prerequisites.
```

```text
Feature: Add AUTH_API_BASE_URL usage in login
README: Update Configuration section with AUTH_API_BASE_URL and example value.
```
